                  <floruit notBefore="1935" notAfter="1938">He was a resistance fighter. 
                     He emerged from being an obscure  <persName ref="PRS5217haylaMa">
                        <roleName type="title">bālābbāt </roleName>
                        Ḫayla Māryām Māmmo
                     </persName>
                     and
                     farmer in <placeName ref="LOC6574NorthSawa"/> to become a national hero during the Italian period, 
                     <date>1935-1941</date>. Early in his life, he was šǝftā and was imprisoned for murder. 
                     However, in the eve of the Italian war of <date>1935-36</date>, 
                     he was pardoned by <persName ref="PRS5226haylase"/> to join the fight against the Italian invasion. 
                     He fought against the Italian forces in several battles in <placeName ref="LOC6574NorthSawa"/>. 
                     His final encounter with the Italians was on <date>06-06-1938</date> 
                     at the battle of <placeName ref="LOC3590Gormes"/> where he was mortally wounded. 
                     
                  </floruit>
                  <death when="1938"/>
                  
                  
